The teenager who killed eight people in a high school shooting in Finland left a suicide note before the attack, police said Thursday.
A teenage killer's deadly school rampage has put Finns on the defensive about their relationship to guns.
The Finnish government has decided at a cabinet meeting on Tuesday to set up a commission of inquiry to investigate the Jokela School shooting in southern Finland, which claimed 8 lives.
The Jokela school shooting in southern Finland last week has spawned a number of threats against other schools, Finnish daily "Helsingin Sanomat" reported Wednesday.
